Package Concepts

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AttributeValue
    This class represents the attribute values of some concepts or individuals.
    AVList
    This class represents lists of attribute values.
    AVObject
    This is the abstract top class for attribute values.
    AVSingleton
    This is the superclass for constrained and unconstrained singleton attribute values.
    AVSingletonConstrained
    This class represents constrained functional attribute values.
    AVSingletonUnconstrained
    This is just a single unconstrained attribute value.
    Concept
    This is an abstract superclass of IndividualConcept and SetConcept.
    DataCarrier
    Instances of this class can be used to fill them with data, transfer them via sockets, and inject them at the destination system into a context.
    DerivedConcept
    A derived concept is a concept which is a subconcept of some superconcepts, together with a filter on the subconcepts of the derived concept.
    IndividualConcept
    This class represents leaf nodes in the concept hierarchy.
    SetConcept
    This concept type represents sets of individuals.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Scope
    A SCOPE specifies the scope of attribute values.
